ConfluencePluginSettings methods have transactions, when this should really be handled at a higher level, especially when the transactions do not appear to nest. See https://atlaseye.atlassian.com/browse/confluence/trunk/confluence-sal-plugin/src/main/java/com/atlassian/sal/confluence/pluginsettings/ConfluencePluginSettings.java

These transactions resulted in a bug in UPM (https://studio.atlassian.com/browse/UPM-410) where an item wasn't getting removed from plugin settings until after it should have been, because there was a valid transaction around the UPM code that called the SAL plugin settings remove method. (UPM worked correctly in RefApp and JIRA.)

